The paper deals with network coding, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). It also involves the computation of rate regions, which is a common theme in network information theory (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the enumeration and hierarchy of networks, which are topics in graph theory and combinatorics, respectively. Therefore, it is likely that the paper could be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
